<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1919-05-03T10:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1919-05-03T10:00:00-05:00" n="619" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d619">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">861.00/4395: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to the Ambassador in Japan</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_MRS1" type="to"><hi rend="italic">Morris</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-05-03T11:00:00-04:00"><hi rend="italic">May 3, 1919,
                                        11 a.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>Your April 29, 3 p.m.</p>
                        <p>Department appreciates friendly and cordial attitude assumed by the
                            Minister of War and hopes our combined efforts may prove successful.</p>
                        <closer><signed><persName corresp="#p_PFL"><hi rend="smallcaps">Polk</hi></persName></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>